---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../site.config';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description={`${SITE.name} is ${SITE.owner}, an independent website builder serving local service businesses in ${SITE.serviceArea} with a deliberately narrow, honestly scoped offer.`}
>
  <header class="page-intro container">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>One person, doing one thing carefully</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      {SITE.name} is me — {SITE.owner}. No sales team, no offshore handoffs,
      no "account managers." The person you talk to is the person who builds
      your site.
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="prose container">
    <h2>Why the scope is narrow</h2>
    <p>
      I build one thing: small, fast, lead-generation websites for local
      service businesses. Not apps, not online stores, not sprawling
      marketing platforms. Keeping the scope narrow is what makes it possible
      to offer a fixed price, a predictable schedule, and a consistent
      standard of work — and to keep getting better at exactly the thing you're
      paying for.
    </p>

    <h2>How I work</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Everything in writing.</strong> Scope, price, schedule, and
        what happens after launch are agreed before work starts.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Evidence over claims.</strong> I don't decorate this site
        with invented praise or client counts. What I show you —
        like the <a href="/work/">Run PSL build</a> — is real and publicly
        verifiable.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>You own your site.</strong> Domain, code, and content stay in
        your hands. My job is to make myself unnecessary, not indispensable.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Plain communication.</strong> You'll get direct answers in
        normal language, including "no" when something isn't worth your
        money.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Where I am</h2>
    <p>
      I'm based on Florida's Treasure Coast and work with businesses
      around {SITE.serviceArea}. Local matters for this kind of site: I know the
      area your customers are searching from.
    </p>

    <h2>The honest position</h2>
    <p>
      I'm early in building this service, and I say so plainly rather than
      dressing this site up as an established agency. What I offer in
      exchange: founding-client pricing, more attention per project than any
      volume shop can give, and a completely inspectable way of working.
      If you'd rather hire a big agency, that's a reasonable choice — but if
      you want a careful builder who treats your project as reputation-making
      work, that's exactly what this is.
    </p>

    <div class="cta-row">
      <a class="btn" href="/contact/">Request a quote</a>
      <a class="btn secondary" href="/work/">See the work</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
